-- Israel to Ease Gaza Restrictions, Allowing Entry of Nonmilitary Supplies
-- Jonathan Ferziger
-- 2010-06-20T15:42:27Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-20/israel-to-ease-gaza-restrictions-allowing-entry-of-nonmilitary-supplies.html

          
          
             Israel agreed to ease its three-
year-old restrictions on the Gaza Strip and allow in any
supplies that are not weapons and don’t have a military use. The
government announced the revision today in a statement on Prime
Minister Benjamin Netanyahu’s website.  
 To contact the reporter on this story:
